verbose_text: Previous studies carried out by Heyen and Schuler [XREF_BIBR] growing MSR-1 under aerobic conditions in medium containing 100 muM ferric citrate determined basal levels of intracellular iron up to 10.8 mg.g -1 of DCW; these cells were classed as only weakly magnetic, probably due to oxygen limitation caused by high biomass concentrations.
